
[1]licentiousness

   LICEN'TIOUSNESS, n. Excessive indulgence of liberty; contempt of the
   just restraints of law, morality and decorum. The licentiousness of
   authors is justly condemned; the licentiousness of the press is
   punishable by law.

   Law is the god of wise men; licentiousness is the god of fools.
